      = '''W''' ([[1981 French Open|1981]])\n| WimbledonDoublesresult            = SF ([[1981 Wimbledon Championships|1981]])\n| USOpenDoublesresult               = QF ([[1978 US Open (tennis)|1978]], [[1981 US Open (tennis)|1981]])\n| OthertournamentsDoubles           = <!-- adds a \"Major doubles tournaments\" title -->\n| MastersCupDoublesresult           =\n| OlympicsDoublesresult             =\n| Mixed                             = <!-- adds mixed information-->\n| mixedtitles                       =\n| mixedrecord                       =\n| AustralianOpenMixedresult         =\n| FrenchOpenMixedresult             = \n| WimbledonMixedresult              = QF ([[1981 Wimbledon Championships|1981]])\n| USOpenMixedresult                 = 1R ([[1980 US Open (tennis)|1980]], [[1980 US Open (tennis)|1980]])\n| Team                              = \n| FedCupresult                      =\n}}\n'''Tanya Harford''' (born 28 November 1958) is a retired South African female [[tennis]] player.<ref>{{cite web|title=WTA \u2013 Player profile|url=http://www.wtatennis.com/players/player/3329/title/tanya-harford|publisher=WTA}}</ref>\n\nIn 1981 she won the doubles title at the [[1981 French Open|French Open]] together with compatriot [[Rosalyn Fairbank]]. In the final they defeated [[Candy Reynolds]] and [[Paula Smith]] in straight sets. Her best result at the [[Wimbledon Championships]] was reaching the third round in the singles in 1980 and 1982 as well as the semifinal in the doubles and the quarterfinal in the mixed doubles event.<ref>{{cite web|title=Wimbledon players archive \u2013 Tanya Harford|url=http://www.wimbledon.com/en_GB/scores/draws/archive/players/9122c3a7-0c09-4111-8241-1275ee49b9c7/index.html|publisher=AELTC}}</ref>\n\nIn 1976 she was a runner-up at the [[Irish Open (tennis)|Irish Open]]. Harford reached the final of the [[South African Open (tennis)|South African Open]] in 1979 but lost in straight sets to [[Brigitte Cuypers]]. With Fairbank she won the doubles title at the [[WTA Swiss Open]] in 1981.\n\nShe served as chair for the Joburg Gay Pride Festival Company, which was organizing the Johannesburg gay pride parade until the dissolution of the company in April 2013,<ref>{{cite web|title=BREAKING: SHOCK AS JOBURG PRIDE SHUTS DOWN|url=http://www.mambaonline.com/2013/04/03/breaking-shock-as-joburg-pride-shuts-down/}}</ref> following controversy over the 2012 edition.<ref>{{cite web|title=Johannesburg gay pride parade pits politics against partying|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2012/oct/09/joburg-gay-pride-clash}}</ref>\n\n\n== Grand Slam finals ==\n===Doubles: 1 (1 title)===\n\n{|class=\"sortable wikitable\" \n!style=\"width:40px\"|Result\n!style=\"width:40px\"|Year\n!style=\"width:150px\"|Championship \n!style=\"width:50px\"|Surface\n!style=\"width:150px\"|Partner\n!style=\"width:150px\"|Opponents\n!style=\"width:110px\" class=\"unsortable\"|Score\n|-bgcolor=\"#EBC2AF\"\n| bgcolor=\"98FB98\"|Win ||[[1981 French Open|1981]] || [[French Open]] || Clay || {{flagicon|RSA|1928}} [[Rosalyn Fairbank]] || {{flagicon|USA}} [[Candy Reynolds]]<br />{{flagicon|USA}} [[Paula Smith]] || 6\u20131, 6\u20133\n|}\n\n==Career finals==\n\n===Singles (1 runner-up)===\n\n{|class=\"sortable wikitable\" \n!style=\"width:40px\"|Result\n!style=\"width:20px\"|W/L\n!style=\"width:60px\"|Date\n!style=\"width:220px\"|Tournament\n!style=\"width:50px\"|Surface\n!style=\"width:140px\"|Opponent\n!style=\"width:100px\" class=\"unsortable\"|Score\n|-\n| style=\"background:#ffa07a;\"|Loss\n| 0\u20131\n| Dec 1979\n| [[1979 South African Open (tennis)|South African Open]], Johannesburg\n| Hard\n| {{flagicon|RSA|1928}} [[Brigitte Cuypers]]\n| 6\u20137, 2\u20136\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{WTA}}\n* {{ITF profile}}\n\n{{French Open women's doubles champions}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Harford, Tanya}}\n[[Category:1958 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:South African female tennis players]]\n[[Category:Grand Slam (tennis) champions in women's doubles]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Cape Town]]\n[[Category:French Open champions]]\n[[Category:White South African people]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=August 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2013}}\n{{Infobox tennis biography\n| name                              = Tanya Harford\n| image                             = \n| caption                           =\n| fullname                          = Tanya Jane Harford Gemmell\n| country                           =  {{flag|South Africa|1928}} \n| residence                         =\n| birth_date                        = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1958|11|28}}\n| birth_place                       = [[Cape Town]], South Africa <ref name=\"who\">{{cite book|editor1-last=Emery|editor1-first=David|title=Who's Who in International Tennis|date=1983|publisher=Sphere|location=London|isbn=9780722133200|pages=52,53}}</ref>\n| death_date                        =\n| death_place                       =\n| height                            = {{height|m=1.62}} <ref name=\"who\"/>\n| college                           =\n| turnedpro                         =\n| retired                           =\n| plays                             =\n| careerprizemoney                  =\n| tennishofyear                     =\n| tennishofid                       =\n| website                           =\n| singlesrecord                     =\n| singlestitles                     =\n| highestsinglesranking             =\n| AustralianOpenresult              = 1R (1980)\n| FrenchOpenresult                  = 2R ([[1982 French Open|1982]])\n| Wimbledonresult                   = 3R ([[1980 Wimbledon Championships|1980]], [[1982 Wimbledon Championships|1982]])\n| USOpenresult                      = 3R ([[1977 US Open (tennis)|1977]])\n| Othertournaments                  = <!-- adds a \"Major tournaments\" title -->\n| MastersCupresult                  =\n| doublesrecord                     =\n| doublestitles         